ullivers Kingdom Temple Walk Matlock Bath Derbyshire DE4 3PG Location driving directions.";i:17;s:31:"Enter DE4 3PG into your SatNav.";i:18;s:78:"If you are on the M1 simply exit Junction 28 and follow the signs to our door.";i:19;s:147:"Gullivers Kingdom is the Derbyshire park in the UK chain of Gullivers theme parks which are primarily aimed at children between 2 and 13 years old.";i:20;s:153:"The parks are named after the title character in the Gullivers Travels stories although these do not feature prominently as a theme at Gullivers Kingdom.";i:21;s:137:"Country park and famous show caverns set in 60 acres of woodland and reached by cable car over deep limestone gorge in the Peak District.";i:22;s:37:"A great family day out in Derbyshire.";i:23;s:37:"6 of 13 things to do in Matlock Bath.";i:24;s:34:"Water Amusement Parks Theme Parks.";i:25;s:67:"Gullivers Kingdom Temple Walk Matlock Bath Matlock DE4 3PG England.";i:26;s:108:"Riding the Chair Lift down to the bottom of the park you disembark through to a conviently placed gift shop.";i:27;s:177:"Beyond this there is a small free arcade with games such as Dont Buzz the Wire game a few mannequins of an old man which most of us would know as Elvis and the Pirate Ship ride.";i:28;s:48:"BRILLIANT PLACE FOR 3-9 YEAR OLDS ABOUT 10 EACH.";i:29;s:86:"Lots of rides but very steep hills we always use the chair lift then work our way dow.";i:30;s:126:"Theres little play places all over like a fun house and a little resturant with a bowling alley large connect 4 and ball pits.";i:31;s:75:"Gullivers Kingdom Temple Walk Matlock Bath Derbyshire DE4 3PG Phone Number.";i:32;s:49:"Visit the Gullivers Kingdom Matlock Bath website.";i:33;s:21:"Opening Hours Prices.";i:34;s:32:"Opening times and ticket prices.";i:35;s:44:"View Gullivers Kingdom Matlock Bath reviews.";i:36;s:26:"View more days out nearby.";i:37;s:53:"Gullivers Kingdom Matlock Bath is a theme Park aimed.";i:38;s:62:"Gullivers Kingdom Temple Walk Matlock Bath Derbyshire DE4 3PG.";i:39;s:29:"Average time spent - 4 hours.";i:40;s:45:"Visit Gullivers Kingdom Matlock Bath website.";i:41;s:27:"Things to do in Derbyshire.";i:42;s:112:"Gullivers Kingdom is a theme park aimed at children aged 3 to 13 in the Derbyshire town of Matlock Bath England.";i:43;s:81:"The park was founded in 1978 by Ray Phillips as a model village for his children.";i:44;s:143:"Gullivers Kingdom is close to the site of the Victorian Switchback rollercoaster ride after which the theme parks main rollercoaster was named.";i:45;s:46:"A hotel and chalets opened in the early 1980s.";i:46;s:154:"Family with young children teenager and wheelchair user - See 1633 traveller reviews 516 candid photos and great deals for Matlock Bath UK at Tripadvisor.";i:47;s:119:"Gullivers Kingdom is a fun-filled adventure with an array of exciting zones and all-weather fun for children aged 2-13.";i:48;s:96:"The whole family can enjoy amazing views of the Peak District National Park from the chair lift.";i:49;s:47:"Little adventurers have a choice of rides from.";i:50;s:91:"Gullivers Kingdom is a family run theme park set on a hill side in Matlock Bath Derbyshire.";i:51;s:117:"I was recently invited to Gullivers on a press event but have been a few times before when Lero and Boo were smaller.";i:52;s:48:"Gullivers really is a great family day out with.";i:53;s:90:"Enjoy beautiful views unique accommodation and a family theme park right on your doorstep.";i:54;s:96:"Enjoy the very best of the Peak District with a short break in our magical themed accommodation.";i:55;s:83:"From swashbuckling pirate cabins promenade rooms princess suites and wizard suites.";i:56;s:67:"Simply choose a date accommodation style and then a package option.";i:57;s:82:"You need an adult per child on the chair lift so make sure you have enough adults.";i:58;s:85:"It is much better value than other theme parks and even in the park it is reasonable.";i:59;s:125:"There are lots of playgrounds all over the place so little ones can play while waiting for bigger children to come off rides.";i:60;s:56:"Wonderful day had- thanks to all the staff at gullivers.";i:61;s:30:"Hotels near Gullivers Kingdom.";i:62;s:175:"005 mi Explorers Retreat at Gullivers Resort Matlock Bath 018 mi Hodgkinsons Hotel 016 mi Birds Nest 020 mi Portland House c1870 - 5 Historic Holiday House 013 mi Charles Bed.";i:63;s:54:"View all hotels near Gullivers Kingdom on Tripadvisor.";i:64;s:86:"Fun day out for younger children but very steep is you have a pushchair or wheelchair.";i:65;s:39:"- See 1614 traveler reviews 500 candid.";i:66;s:131:"The Gullivers Kingdom theme park at Milton Keynes is the oldest of the Gullivers theme parks and is showing its age in some places.";i:67;s:60:"It could certainly do with some refurbishment in some areas.";i:68;s:94:"The park is not quite as good as the Gulliver Land Theme Park but is still well worth a visit.";i:69;s:51:"A great day out and thoroughly enjoyed by our kids.";}}